Vulnerability Scanner

A simple, command-line vulnerability scanner to analyze web applications for common security issues and export scan reports in CSV, JSON, and HTML formats.

**Features:
Scans target URLs for security vulnerabilities (XSS, SQLi, open redirects, and more)

Command-line interface for easy use

Generates scan results in multiple formats: CSV, JSON, HTML

Color-coded console output for clarity

Safe for demos and educational security testing

**Requirements:
Python 3.7+

**Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt


**TO RUN
python scanner.py <url>
Example:
python scanner.py https://juice-shop.herokuapp.com
                  http://testphp.vulnweb.com
                  https://www.google.com
                  https://httpbin.org
                
**The scan results will be saved as:
scan_report.csv
scan_report.json
scan_report.html